The Brandvlei Correctional Centre has launched the continent's first-ever prison radio station. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG – The Brandvlei Correctional Centre has launched the continent’s first-ever prison radio station. Basic Radio 98.7 is digital and operated by inmates. WATCH: Inside South Africa's secure prison Correctional Services Minister Ronald Lamola recently launched the station and was on air alongside prominent radio personality, Phat Joe. “I’m here with a message. I’m going to take this station nationwide. You guys will be heard coast to coast. I’m talking to your managers and programme directors right now”, said Phat Joe. 